Package: pygtk2-py23
Version: 1.99.17
Revision: 1
Description: Python bindings for the GTK widget set
DescDetail: <<
PyGTK provides an object oriented interface that is slightly higher
level than the C one. It automatically does all the type casting and
reference counting that you would have to do normally with the C API.

One can have both pygtk and pygtk2 installed at the same time, but not
both in the same python.
<<
DescPort: <<
To allow both pygtk and pygtk2 concurrently on the system but forbid
in the same python, the unversioned pygtk2 placeholder package has no
Conflicts/Replaces, but the versioned pygtk2-py* packages each have
Conflicts/Replaces for the analogous pygtk-py* package.

Removed -no-undefined: http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=118841

Patched atk.override: http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=118835

Patched examples/ to use the desired python interpretter.

The widget demo share/pygtk2-py23/examples/pygtk-demo works, but some
of the other examples in examples/* do not (for a variety of reasons).

Originally ported by Michel Alexandre Salim <salimma@users.sourceforge.net>
(up to pygtk2-1.99.15-1)
<<
